A brand new brick manufacturing factory has been opened in Carletonville, Gauteng. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A brand new brick manufacturing factory has been opened in Carletonville, Gauteng. Corobrik's Kwastina brick factory is an R800-million investment and is expected to boost the local economy. WATCH: Ramaphosa opens brick factory President Cyril Ramaphosa delivered the keynote address at the opening. The president also welcomed the investment, saying it was made to one of South Africa's biggest employers, the manufacturing sector. 